				<li id="16604497" class="cmnt-root" data="43" data-d="1649397397000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578393/Dragonbolt-Blessing" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Apr 2022 01:56</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16604497" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Considerably increases the viability of Raptor of the Mists. Makes it so that if an R1 triggers the dodge, they will be bounced and unable to combo the initial hit or roll out of the follow-up jump attack. Most large/heavy weapons won&apos;t be fast enough to hit you in the air before you counter, so really the only counter to this outside of ranged attacks/pokes is for the enemy to be 2-handing a katana. As they are 2h-ing they will not get bounced off on the triggering attack, and katanas are fast and long enough to clip you with a second attack whilst you&apos;re in the air.<br/><br/>It&apos;s not an &quot;EZ win&quot; but it definitely increases the viability of RotM in PvP.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16604497" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16604497" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>43</p><i class=