				<li id="16555093" class="cmnt-root" data="-2" data-d="1647943645000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578393/Dragonbolt-Blessing" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Mar 2022 06:07</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16555093" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">&quot;reduce lightning damage negation by 35%&quot; is incorrect and vague. The 2 ways this can be interpreted are that it takes a flat 35% off of your lightning damage negation, or that it cuts 35% of your lightning damage negation away, IE, with 10 lightning damage negation you&apos;d be reduced to 6.5% lightning damage negation. Both these interpretations are wrong. At 25% lightning damage negation it reduces me to 0% lightning damage negation. Another person reported it reduced his lightning damage negation from 46% to 28%. What this actually does is increase the lightning damage you take by about 1/3 or 33%.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16555093" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16555093" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>12</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>14</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16555093"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16555093" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16555093"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16552262" class="cmnt-root" data="37" data-d="1647874521000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578393/Dragonbolt-Blessing" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Mar 2022 10:55</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16552262" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is massively underrated in PVP. In invasions, you can punish people who think they can dogpile you with r1 spam.  In duals, it counters 2 very prominent builds in the meta, fingerprint shieldpoke and dual seppuku bleed builds. It&apos;s virtually a hardcounter versus greatshield poke builds if you&apos;re running high poise, even great spear R1s will bounce off you and puts them out of their blocking state while you get a free follow up.  Versus dual seppuku katanas and spears, it&apos;s more of a softcounter as it stacks with other sources of bleed resistance and the bouncing effect keeps them from getting guaranteed combos if you bleed and get stunned.  Against seppuku twinblades and WA bleed build (namely Rivers of Blood), not as effective since they won&apos;t bounce off but the bleed resist is still nice.  Technically this is also true against other forms of status builds, you can use this and Speckled Hardtear to get high resistances to all status effects.  Also just pretty good in general, most people don&apos;t know what it does, so you will probably win against anyone using sword and board playstyles.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16552262" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16552262" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>38</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16552262"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16552262" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16552262"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16552174" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1647874484000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578393/Dragonbolt-Blessing" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Mar 2022 10:54</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16552174" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is massively underrated in PVP. In invasions, you can punish people who think they can dogpile you with r1 spam.  In duals, it counters 2 very prominent builds in the meta, fingerprint shieldpoke and dual seppuku bleed builds. It&apos;s virtually a hardcounter versus greatshield poke builds if you&apos;re running high poise, even great spear R1s will bounce off you and puts them out of their blocking state while you get a free follow up.  Versus dual seppuku katanas and spears, it&apos;s more of a softcounter as it stacks with other sources of bleed resistance and the bouncing effect keeps them from getting guaranteed combos if you bleed and get stunned.  Against seppuku twinblades and WA bleed build (namely Rivers of Blood), not as effective since they won&apos;t bounce off but the bleed resist is still nice.  Technically this is also true against other forms of status builds, you can use this and Speckled Hardtear to get high resistances to all status effects.  Also just pretty good in general, most people don&apos;t know what it does, so you will probably win against anyone using sword and board playstyles.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="butto